# Quickstart

This guide will help you get {{ project_name }} up and running quickly.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

- Python 3.11 or later
- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) package manager
{%- if api_tracks in ['node', 'python+node'] %}
- Node.js 20 LTS or later
- pnpm 8 or later
{%- endif %}

## Installation

### Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{ project_slug }}/{{ project_slug }}.git
cd {{ project_slug }}
```

### Install Dependencies

```bash
# Install Python dependencies
uv sync

{%- if api_tracks in ['node', 'python+node'] %}
# Install Node.js dependencies
pnpm install
{%- endif %}
```

### Configure Environment

```bash
# Copy the example environment file
cp .env.example .env

# Edit .env with your settings
```

## Development

{%- if cli_module == 'enabled' %}

### Running the CLI

```bash
uv run {{ package_name }} --help
```
{%- endif %}

{%- if api_tracks in ['python', 'python+node'] %}

### Starting the API Server

```bash
uv run uvicorn {{ package_name }}.api.main:app --reload
```

The API will be available at `http://localhost:8000`.
{%- endif %}

{%- if api_tracks in ['node', 'python+node'] %}

### Starting Node.js Services

```bash
pnpm dev
```
{%- endif %}

## Running Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
uv run pytest

# Run with coverage
uv run pytest --cov
```

